{
  "text": "VPC peering creates a direct network connection between two VPCs, allowing them to communicate as if they were on the same network. Peering as one-to-one each peering connection connects exactly two VPCs. It's useful for connecting VPCs in the same region or different regions. Peering is non-transitive, meaning if VPC-A peers with VPC-BP, and VPC-B peers with VPC-C, VPC-A cannot reach VPC-B, peers with V-ring connections for each peering connections.",
